					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13964437#post-4856667</guid>
				<title>Through the Author, All Posts are Possible</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13964437/scp-3178#post-4856667</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 29 Dec 2020 15:07:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>UraniumEmpire</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1613974</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div style="text-align: center;"> <p><em><a href="https://youtu.be/AGDY4r951Zc">The God you believe in is not only not good.</a></em><br /> <em><a href="https://youtu.be/AGDY4r951Zc">That God is cruel.</a></em></p> </div> <hr /> <p>In 9th grade, I watched a documentary about the Russian Revolution, which ended on what was clearly meant to be a feel-good note with the Russian Orthodox Church canonizing Nicholas II. I'm thankful my ancestors, refugees from the Tsar's cruelty, weren't around to see such a thing.</p> <p>Thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jackalrelated" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3207203&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609254425" alt="JackalRelated" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3207203)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jackalrelated" >JackalRelated</a></span> for <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5050">SCP-5050</a>, which heavily inspired the structure of this piece. Additionally, thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609254425" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" >Ihp</a></span> for helping me come up with the name for a nexus highway, and thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609254425" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" >stormbreath</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jackalrelated" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3207203&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609254425" alt="JackalRelated" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3207203)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jackalrelated" >JackalRelated</a></span> for the crit.</p> <p>Part three of Christ In Scarlet.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Translation&nbsp;notes</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <ul> <li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><em>DO NOT HAVE MAISIE CALL THE BABY A BABY</em></strong></span>. She does not see it as a baby, but as an undead abomination. The Foundation is allowed to call it a baby.</li> <li>Mrs. Davis's dialogue was written under the assumption that she fears and reviles the god she's talking about.</li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> <p><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kossuth-buildings-NE-ms.jpg">whitewater</a><br /> <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Abandoned_houses,_Natchez,_Mississippi_LCCN2010630793.tif">throughgod</a></p> 
				 	]]>
